{
  "text": "16 week old male wild-type (WT) mice and sg/sg littermates were obtained from crossing heterozygous sg/+, B6.C3(Cg)-Rorα sg /J. Animals were housed in the Queensland Bioscience Precinct Vivarium (UQ) with a 12 h light-dark cycle and feeding has been previously described [CITATION_1] . Mice were fasted for 6 h and euthanized by CO 2 asphyxiation. All aspects of animal experimentation were approved by The University of Queensland Animal Ethics Committee.",
